\begin_layout Standard
Assisted with the developments in game theory and an improvement in the
 quality of microdata from consumption surveys, an interest in Veblen's
 observations has been revived in the recent years (see Frank 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "FrankPond,FrankModel"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, Hirsch 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "HirschSocialLimits"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and Koustobinas
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "KoutsobinasStatusPoliticalEconomy"
literal "false"

\end_inset

).
 We argue that this recent attention to status consumption need not to be
 viewed asunder from the consumer demand literature on habit-formation (see
 for example Muellbauer 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "MuellbauerRationalityMyopia1988."
literal "true"

\end_inset

's discussion of the myopia amongst consumers and Fisher-Shell
